Object.Field: Configuration #3 - IKM Oracle Partition Exchange Load - Synchronous - Flow Control - With Validation

This package uses the scenarios of the mapping called "03 - Warehouse.Facts.Orders - IKM Oracle Partition Exchange Load - With Validation & Flow Control" to perform a full load of the partitioned table.
The scenarios in this package use Oracle Partition Exchange to perform the full load of the partitioned table with the IKM Oracle Partition Exchange Load.
This package performs the partition exchange operation with validation. Flow control is used as well. The flow control option invokes the CKM Oracle to validate the source data before the exchange operation.
The first scenario changes the statistics preference of the table to incremental. Table constraints are not disabled. The next set of partitions is loaded sequentially.
The last scenario gathers incremental stats.
Local and global indexes are not rebuilt in any of the scenarios. Both type of indexes are USUABLE during the entire upload operation due to the following partition exchange options:
INCLUDING INDEXES UPDATE INDEXES PARALLEL
This strategy offers the following benefits:
1. Data is clean before the exchange operation (flow control) 2. Constraints stay enabled during the entire upload operation. 3. There is no need to rebuild local or global indexes, since the exchange operation is done with local indexes, and global indexes are updated. 4. Both, local and global indexes stay USABLE during the entire upload operation; thus, users can use the indexes of the partitioned table to query the data. 4. Stats are gathered at the end.
Disadvantages: 1. The exchange operation takes longer to complete because it needs to update global indexes. 2. The partitions are uploaded sequentially (see NOTE below), increasing the overall time it takes to perform the full upload operation of the partitioned table. 3. Since constraints are enabled during the exchange operation and the exchange is done WITH VALIDATION, the upload operation takes additional time.
The package waits 5 seconds before launching the next partition upload. This is to ensure that the PARTITION_MONTH variable gets refreshed accordingly before assigning its value to the next scenario.
NOTE: The load is done in synchronous mode (sequentially). This is due to a limitation in the CKM Oracle. The CKM Oracle does not create UNQUE AK indexes for each flow table that is created by each scenario; thus, flow tables without indexes will perform poorly. To avoid performance problems, the scenarios are being executed in synchronous mode. The CKM Oracle index limitation will be fixed in future versions of ODI.
